  <discussion>Fimbristylis squarrosa is an Old World temperate to tropical weed, mostly of Asia and Africa.</discussion>
  <discussion>While Fimbristylis squarrosa has been collected only once in North America from ballast at Camden, New Jersey (C. F. Parker, in 1865), the weedy and often ruderal nature of the species makes it a likely future adventive.</discussion>
